   ultimately approach or avoid others may depend on such judgments.
   Method: We used functional magnetic resonance imaging to determine the
   neural basis for such approachability judgments and the relationship
   between these judgments and trait anxiety. Participants viewed ambiguous
   (i.e. neutral) or relatively unambiguous (i.e. angry, happy) faces,
